article.headline: Binghamton 64, Stony Brook 57
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Troy Hailey had 14 points and Brandon Carter added 13 and Binghamton rallied for a 64-57 victory over Stony Brook on Sunday by holding the Seawolves without a field goal over the final 6:20. Nick Billings added 12 points, 11 in the second half, for the Bearcats (13-14, 9-7 America East). Mitchell Beauford scored 22 points for the Seawolves (8-17, 5-11) and D.J. Munir had 14. A layup by Beauford with 6:20 to play gave Stony Brook a 51-48 lead. The Bearcats then went on a 7-0 run, the last four points from Billings, to go in front 55-51 with 4:48 left. Two free throws each by Beauford and Munir tied it, but Hailey had four points as Binghamton closed the game with a 9-2 run. Billings' jumper with 3:33 left put the Bearcats ahead for good at 57-55. Two free throws by Hailey with 27 seconds left gave them their biggest lead down the stretch, 60-55.
